User Case: Select a dropdown menu option

Actors: User

Goal: Allow the user to view the options of the menu and select one

Preconditions: User is on the page that contains a dropdown menu and the dropdown menu is loaded and visible.

Postconditions: The system or website registers the selected option and updates the interface if an error occurs no option is selected and the system prompts to try again. 

Main Flow: 
1. The user navigates to the page containing the dropdown menu
2. User clicks on the dropdown menu
3. The system expands the menu and displays the list of avalible options
4. User selects one option from the list 
5. System registers the option and updates the interface of the user. 

